= Abstract

Apollon is a UML Diagram Editor designed to help students create diagrams easily. However, many users find it hard to use, which affects its popularity, especially on both web and mobile platforms. This thesis aims to fix key usability problems and redesign the interface for a better user experience. The main focus is improving the design, fixing bugs, and adding useful features. The desired outcome is to make Apollon easier to use for everyone, helping students to create diagrams smoothly.